bilingual.source: He kept sighing as he read the disappointing news.
bilingual.target: 他在读到令人失望的消息时不断叹气。

bilingual.source: Ingratitude is one of the most disappointing qualities.
bilingual.target: 忘恩负义是最令人失望的品质之一。

bilingual.source: She felt downbeat after hearing the disappointing news.
bilingual.target: 听到令人失望的消息后，她感到沉闷。

bilingual.source: The company's shares were oversold after the disappointing earnings report.
bilingual.target: 该公司股票在令人失望的收益报告后超卖。

bilingual.source: I started my new English class last week, which was a really disappointing experience since the teacher was not a native speaker.
bilingual.target: 我上周开始了我的新英语课，这是一次非常令人失望的经历，因为老师不是以英语为母语的人。
这对我们来说是非常令人失望的。

bilingual.source: It may be a disappointing day emotionally.
bilingual.target: 情感上可能是令人失望的一天。

bilingual.source: We noticed a disappointing look on his face.
bilingual.target: 我们注意到他脸上一种令人失望的表情。

bilingual.source: Our team had a disappointing winless season.
bilingual.target: 我们的队伍经历了一个令人失望的,毫无胜绩的赛季.

bilingual.source: Our choices can turn out to be disappointing.
bilingual.target: 我们的选择可能最终是令人失望的。

yingyinNormal.en: Yes, disappointing fathers. Tell me about it. I remember for my 16th birthday, my dad bought me a Mercedes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是啊，令人失望的父亲们。可不是咋的。我还记得我16岁生日，我爸给我买了奔驰。

yingyinNormal.en: Our surest way of disappointing him will be to ask nothing about it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 让他失望是最好的办法，什么都不问他。

yingyinNormal.en: But so often, they turn out to be, I don't know, disappointing and stupid.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是，她们总变得，我不知道，让人失望，变得愚蠢。

yingyinNormal.en: Better than God's Cauldron, I hope. Sales were disappointing, weren't they?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我希望比《上帝之釜》要好，销量不高，是吗？

yingyinNormal.en: And suffered the same fate. It's a disappointing end to her story, isn't it?
yingyinNormal.zh: 结果落得相同的下场，真是个令人遗憾的结局，对吧？

yingyinNormal.en: Well, that's disappointing. I've always wanted to be invited to a slumber party.
yingyinNormal.zh: 太让人失望了，我一直都想被人邀请去睡衣派对的。

yingyinNormal.en: In fact, they've been disappointing on everything you've written the past ten years.
yingyinNormal.zh: 事实上，你过去十年写的每一本书销量都不高。

yingyinNormal.en: Anyway, you ended up disappointing me more than, more than any of the other silly girls.
yingyinNormal.zh: 总之，你却比其他任何蠢女孩都更让我感到失望。

yingyinNormal.en: No, no, he would never be that disappointing. He's planned something, something long-term.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不，不，他不会那么让人失望的，他肯定计划好了什么，长期计划。

yingyinNormal.en: I've had a long and rather disappointing day, so yeah, I should probably get to sleep now.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我今天累了，也有点儿失望，或许该睡了。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm afraid you may find us disappointing guests if you want us to stay up till two in the morning being witty.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们俩昨晚熬到凌晨两点，恐怕今天是做不到风趣诙谐了。

yingyinNormal.en: And next. If either of us ever invents time travel, we agree our first stop will be this meeting today in precisely five seconds. Okay. That's disappointing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 下一条，如果我们之中任何一人发明了时空穿梭机，我们同意第一站就是回到今天这个会议，时间是5秒之后。好。真可惜。

yingyinNormal.en: As I was saying, you and Leonard had a disappointing sexual encounter. Earlier this evening, Leonard characterized as just fine. So what you're seeing here is a continuation of the mocking that followed.
yingyinNormal.zh: 言归正传，你和莱纳德的性爱比较失望。今天傍晚，莱纳德将其描述为“挺好”，所以你看到的只是嘲笑的后续篇。
